{
  "answer": "**Vratisasana, Chapter 1**\n\nThis warning to ascetics (*viku*) appears in the commentary to verse 32 (VS_32), which warns of the consequences for failing to protect moral conduct (*śīla*, the \"five precepts and ten virtues\"):<sup>[1]</sup>\n\n> That sacred thread will become a club, a mace to beat your body there in the world of Yama, if the *śīla* is not protected by you. [...] Likewise, the sacred ash of the *viku* will become a mountain of fire, burning your body there in the world of Yama, if the *śīla* is not protected by you. [...] And so too the rosary, which is the counter for the *viku*, will become an instrument of punishment for your faults. How long will they be counted and laid out? A hundred years of punishment for each bead, if the *śīla* is not protected by you.\n\n[^1]: *Vratisasana*, [Chapter 1](/works/unknown-vratisasana-d0fe75/01/translation/#p-a8364a).",
